Sacyr to Issue as Much as 230 Million Euros in Convertibles

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 
2011-03-31T16:25:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/sacyr-to-issue-as-much-as-eu299-million-in-convertibles-1-.html
Sacyr Vallehermoso SA (SYV)  said it will
issue as much as 230 million euros ($326 million) of convertible
bonds with a coupon of 6.5 percent.  The initial conversion price is 10.61 euros per share, the
Madrid-based construction company and property developer said
today in a regulatory filing.  Sacyr said earlier today it had hired  Societe Generale (GLE)  to
lead the sale of as much as 299 million euros of bonds
convertible in shares before May 1, 2016, with a coupon of 5.75
percent to 6.5 percent.  Shares in Sacyr fell 2 percent today to 8.20 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
 ssmyth2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Blackman at   ablackman@bloomberg.net . 